-- Russian stocks fall after reports Ukraine secession vote to go ahead 
-- 
-- Thu May 08, 2014 06:08AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, May 8 (Reuters) - Russian stocks <.MCX> <.IRTS> turned negative on Thursday after Interfax news agency reported that a referendum on possible secession would go ahead in eastern Ukraine on May 11, despite Russian President Vladimir Putin's call for the vote to be postponed.

